Starting on Monday, September 14, there will be OPTIONAL 7-12 volleyball, 7 & 8 football, and 9-12 football practices.

**These are not required practices; this is an opportunity given by MSHSL to allow athletes and coaches to get together to practice since there is no fall season.**

For more information, call or stop in the MS/HS Office, or visit desch.org/page/3390. No participation fee will be charged for these practices.

post_text:
Dear Dover-Eyota families,

Please consider taking time to respond to the parent survey below in the message from the Minnesota Department of Education. School districts across the state have been directed to design multiple plans for opening school this fall. The survey is available in English, Hmong, Somali, and Spanish.

With your feedback in mind, MDE will be providing guidance to all school districts on how to best plan ahead with three possible scenarios:

1. Return all students to school buildings following the most current CDC and MDH guidelines.

2. Return students to school buildings, implementing a hybrid model following the most current CDC and MDH guidelines.

3. No students return to school buildings. Implement a distance learning model.

This is a challenging time for all of us. As we begin the process for designing possible schedules, our Dover-Eyota planning team will also invite you to provide us with your feedback.

Here is the link: http://sgiz.mobi/s3/2020-Parent-Distance-Learning-Feedback-Survey

Thank you,

Mike Carolan - Superintendent

Dover-Eyota Schools

The Dover-Eyota school library will be available to the community to pick up library books!

Please visit the school website at desch.org, and you can find our library catalog on the student links page. Look for "Elementary Follett Destiny or MS/HS Follett Destiny." Search for the books you want (make sure they are listed as available) and email barbkingsley@deschools.org to order. She will pull books on Tuesday mornings (starting on June 16th) and place them in a pick up box in the elementary front entry.

Happy reading!

Minnesota is now offering funds for families of children ages 5 to 18 who qualify for free or reduced-price school meals.

The new program, called Pandemic EBT (P-EBT), will provide up to $325 per child that families can use to purchase nutritious food for their household. Approximately 350,000 Minnesota children could benefit!

Learn more at www.mn.p-ebt.org .

post_text:
Last week, our seniors added their handprints to the Class of 2020's mural at Dover-Eyota High School. Senior student Kaylee Hammel painted this work of art, and helped other students add their handprints to the wall. (Laura Kase photos)

Part of the mural reads, "2020: A class that was born during the year of 9/11, and graduated under a global pandemic. Through it all, we became stronger and conquered adversity TOGETHER."

This weekend, our senior students will receive their diplomas. We wish the school year could have ended differently, but we are still so proud of our seniors, and all they have accomplished. We wish you all the best, graduates!

Check out this great video, featuring Dover-Eyota fourth and fifth grade PE students! These students were asked to contribute to the video for their Physical Education Rhythms Unit. For this project, the students practiced teamwork, organization, creativity, and kept the rhythm for an 8-count beat (to the song Another One Bites the Dust, by Queen.) This was a fun way to end a crazy fourth quarter!

This video was edited by D-E alumni, Tyler Aeschlimann, and features Mr. Eric Aeschlimann as Superman, and Mr. Ryan Scheevel as Spiderman!

HAS YOUR INCOME CHANGED IN THE PAST FEW MONTHS?

If the answer is yes, please consider applying or reapplying Application for Educational Benefits State and Federally Funded Programs for Schools. During these difficult economic times, you may have lost income, which is a determining factor for the approval.

If approved, the school district receives additional funding for a variety of programs, including State, Federal, and Title I funding for school resources like books, computers, and classroom equipment.

Applications for Educational Benefits are available at www.desch.org/page/3605.

Mrs. Rhea (K-12 Media Specialist) got an email this morning from Skoob the shelf elf and Mr. Wiggles the bookworm! They want to know where all the kids have gone!

The email says:
"Hi Mrs. Rhea,
We noticed that it has been really quiet in the library. Do you know where the kids are? We miss them! Mr. Wiggles and I went searching for them and the Dr. Seuss Characters helped us film. The Lorax moved, so we had part of a blurry video. I don't think he can film next time.  Anyway, if you don't know where they are, could you send this video to Mrs. Kase? Maybe she can put it on the school site to help us solve the mystery.
Your friends,
Skoob the shelf elf and Mr. Wiggles the bookworm"

Watch Episode 1 now, and email shelfelf@deschools.org to let Skoob and Mr. Wiggles know what you're up to!

post_text:
Yesterday, Dover-Eyota Public Schools and Jostens provided a drive-thru cap and gown pick-up service for our senior students! 

Staff members made colorful banners for the seniors, which shared positive messages: We Love You! and We are Proud of You! Danielle and Diane even painted the windows of the building with more positive messages, including: We miss you and your smiles! Staff members spread out on the sidewalk, and cheered for the seniors as they stopped by. (We tried to stand six feet apart, and used lots of hand sanitizer!)

Thank you to our staff members, and Paul and Joe from Jostens, for making this a memorable day for our senior students, and to Carrie Frank, for creating this great video.

WE MISS OUR STUDENTS!

Today, while practicing social distancing, Dover-Eyota Elementary School staff sang You Are My Sunshine. They were accompanied by D-E Elementary Vocal Music Instructor Mrs. Kathryn Kabes on the piano. Here are the new lyrics:

You are My Sunshine
You are my sunshine, my only sunshine.
You make us happy when skies are gray.
Youll never know dears how much we love you
Please dont take our sunshine away.

You know we miss you when you are not here.
Please stay connected if you can.
Well all do our best to keep on learning.
Until we see you again.

There will be reading and therell be math too
Keep on checking as you can.
We want to keep up on our learning.
Until we see you again.

You are my sunshine, my only sunshine.
You make us happy when skies are gray.
Youll never know dears how much we love you
Please dont take our sunshine away.

post_text:
Here is the latest information from Dover-Eyota Schools (updated on Sunday evening, 3/15/20.)

I participated in a webinar with MREA on Sunday evening and they clarified the question about child care.

Child care will be free to health care and emergency provider families. There is a concern about our capacity to serve a large number of children in grades K-Grade 5. We will need to assign personnel such as paras, bus drivers, food service workers to fill in as our child care staff during this emergency time.

I appreciate your patience as we plan the educational needs of our students. We have many other considerations to plan for including how we can support our staff through this process. I will be continuing to monitor advisories from the state. Look for a resource tab on the website very soon.

Mike Carolan

This Saturday, March 14, our friends at the Dover-Eyota Eagles Foundation are hosting the 2020 Dover-Eyota Specialty Auction at the Eyota American Legion. Please consider attending!

For more information, please visit https://www.facebook.com/events/321956378750571/permalink/328201921459350

The money raised at the auction will be used to assist with capital projects (specifically outdoor bathrooms at the track and playing field), promoting school spirit in the community, and healthy living. The foundation also has setup a bi-annual grant program for Dover-Eyota area organizations to submit requests for funds.

post_text: Thank you to Goldenrust Farm for helping make it possible for our students to enjoy local (and D-E Licious!) foods!
shared_text:
Goldenrust Farm is with Jessica Desens and 4 others at Dover-Eyota Public Schools.
March 5 at 2:21 PM 路 Eyota, MN 路

Today we participated in #mnthurs with Dover-Eyota Schools! The elementary school serves hot dogs from our farm, and the high school serves hamburgers from our farm! It's pretty awesome to see something we grew in our local school. My dream is that someday this is a common practice in all schools throughout the state.
See the full story tonight on ABC 6 news!! #farmily #beef #local #winwin #farm2school @ Dover-Eyota Public Schools

shared_text:
Dover Eyota Music Association - DEMAPops and Pie 2020
February 2 at 11:09 AM 路

Pops and Pie is an important fundraiser for DEMA! Wondering what DEMA does with the funds they raise? Here are just a few of the things they have purchased for the Dover Eyota Band and Choir programs... new choir risers, new sound shells, new choir folders, a Capella t-shirts for Minor Details, t-shirts for honors band and choir, repairing donated instruments, cleanings for school owned instruments, buying new instruments, paying part of the cost of the MMEA clinic for our music teachers, guest clinicians such as Sam Hazo and Copper Street Brass, and a Marching Band assistant. They have also helped cover the cost for the new Timpani and the 6th grade keyboard, among many other items and opportunities.
Pops and Pie is Saturday, February 8 at the Eyota American Legion starting at 3:00. Come support the arts.

Pops and Pie is an important fundraiser for DEMA! Wondering what DEMA does with the funds they raise? Here are just a few of the things they have purchased for the Dover Eyota Band and Choir programs... new choir risers, new sound shells, new choir folders, a Capella t-shirts for Minor Details, t-shirts for honors band and choir, repairing donated instruments, cleanings for school owned instruments, buying new instruments, paying part of the cost of the MMEA clinic for our music teachers, guest clinicians such as Sam Hazo and Copper Street Brass, and a Marching Band assistant. They have also helped cover the cost for the new Timpani and the 6th grade keyboard, among many other items and opportunities.
Pops and Pie is Saturday, February 8 at the Eyota American Legion starting at 3:00. Come support the arts.
